WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.175 align:middle line:90%


00:00:06.175 --> 00:00:07.430 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:07.430 --> 00:00:12.470 align:middle line:84%
>> Somehow or other, our minds
are able to access a connection

00:00:12.470 --> 00:00:15.260 align:middle line:84%
independently of
distance and time.

00:00:15.260 --> 00:00:19.430 align:middle line:84%
>> If you get that contact
realizing that there is

00:00:19.430 --> 00:00:21.340 align:middle line:90%
a source to everything.

00:00:21.340 --> 00:00:26.150 align:middle line:84%
>> We don't have the English
words to describe what happens

00:00:26.150 --> 00:00:27.080 align:middle line:90%
in that experience.

00:00:27.080 --> 00:00:28.460 align:middle line:90%
What is this showing me?

00:00:28.460 --> 00:00:32.670 align:middle line:84%
What is it's showing us as
human beings about who we are?

00:00:32.670 --> 00:00:36.200 align:middle line:84%
>> We can use this as a form
of guidance that lights our way

00:00:36.200 --> 00:00:38.529 align:middle line:90%
along the path of life.

00:00:38.529 --> 00:00:42.022 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:42.022 --> 00:01:14.490 align:middle line:90%


00:01:14.490 --> 00:01:18.150 align:middle line:84%
>> My daddy and I had
traveled in Egypt many times.

00:01:18.150 --> 00:01:22.200 align:middle line:10%
But on this particular
occasion, early in 1996,

00:01:22.200 --> 00:01:26.400 align:middle line:10%
we found ourselves in the King's
Chamber of the Great Pyramid

00:01:26.400 --> 00:01:29.340 align:middle line:10%
all alone, which was a
very unusual occurrence.

00:01:29.340 --> 00:01:32.010 align:middle line:10%
Prior to this, we'd
always been surrounded

00:01:32.010 --> 00:01:34.050 align:middle line:10%
by so many other people.

00:01:34.050 --> 00:01:35.850 align:middle line:10%
Well, for those of
you who've actually

00:01:35.850 --> 00:01:37.620 align:middle line:10%
experienced the
King's Chamber, you'll

00:01:37.620 --> 00:01:40.890 align:middle line:10%
know that it has an
extraordinary acoustic quality.

00:01:40.890 --> 00:01:45.810 align:middle line:84%
This sarcophagus is a
block of granite 3.7 tons

00:01:45.810 --> 00:01:47.590 align:middle line:90%
that's been hollowed out.

00:01:47.590 --> 00:01:51.540 align:middle line:84%
It's supposed to be the
interment for King Khufu

00:01:51.540 --> 00:01:52.380 align:middle line:90%
or Cheops.

00:01:52.380 --> 00:01:54.510 align:middle line:84%
Many people disagree
with that concept.

00:01:54.510 --> 00:01:58.500 align:middle line:84%
But nevertheless, if you strike
the side of it with your fist,

00:01:58.500 --> 00:02:01.080 align:middle line:84%
it rings like a
low-pitched bell.

00:02:01.080 --> 00:02:04.570 align:middle line:84%
And, of course, as an acoustics
engineer at that time,

00:02:04.570 --> 00:02:08.639 align:middle line:84%
I was fascinated by the
sounds that sarcophagus made.

00:02:08.639 --> 00:02:13.380 align:middle line:84%
So I'd always wanted to lie in
the sarcophagus and make sound.

00:02:13.380 --> 00:02:16.210 align:middle line:84%
And never until this
time in early '96

00:02:16.210 --> 00:02:18.040 align:middle line:90%
did I have the opportunity.

00:02:18.040 --> 00:02:20.770 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, I did lie
in the sarcophagus

00:02:20.770 --> 00:02:23.140 align:middle line:90%
and I made a vocal glissando.

00:02:23.140 --> 00:02:27.580 align:middle line:84%
And at one particular
frequency, every cell in my body

00:02:27.580 --> 00:02:28.960 align:middle line:90%
seemed to tingle.

00:02:28.960 --> 00:02:33.490 align:middle line:84%
And a wave of acoustic energy
washed up and down my body,

00:02:33.490 --> 00:02:37.840 align:middle line:84%
and goosebumps broke
out all over my flesh.

00:02:37.840 --> 00:02:41.470 align:middle line:84%
And it really got my
attention and I thought, wow,

00:02:41.470 --> 00:02:46.420 align:middle line:84%
having at that point in my
career spent almost 30 years

00:02:46.420 --> 00:02:50.440 align:middle line:84%
studying sound in various
acoustics environments,

00:02:50.440 --> 00:02:53.570 align:middle line:84%
I'd never come across
anything quite like this.

00:02:53.570 --> 00:02:56.080 align:middle line:84%
So when we got back to
the UK, I made enquiries

00:02:56.080 --> 00:02:58.300 align:middle line:90%
with the Egyptian authorities.

00:02:58.300 --> 00:02:59.620 align:middle line:90%
It was not easy.

00:02:59.620 --> 00:03:02.140 align:middle line:84%
But several months
later, I returned

00:03:02.140 --> 00:03:08.340 align:middle line:84%
to Egypt armed with lots of
acoustics instrumentation.

00:03:08.340 --> 00:03:11.580 align:middle line:84%
About three weeks before
going out to Egypt in '97,

00:03:11.580 --> 00:03:14.100 align:middle line:84%
I severely injured
my lower back.

00:03:14.100 --> 00:03:17.220 align:middle line:84%
And, oh, my goodness,
the pain was very severe.

00:03:17.220 --> 00:03:19.500 align:middle line:84%
And it was so severe
that I actually

00:03:19.500 --> 00:03:22.620 align:middle line:84%
thought I was going to have
to cancel the whole mission.

00:03:22.620 --> 00:03:25.510 align:middle line:84%
But I paid a lot of money
to the Egyptian Antiquities

00:03:25.510 --> 00:03:26.310 align:middle line:90%
Department.

00:03:26.310 --> 00:03:29.310 align:middle line:10%
So I just gritted my
teeth and somehow I

00:03:29.310 --> 00:03:32.130 align:middle line:10%
managed to get myself
into the Great Pyramid.

00:03:32.130 --> 00:03:35.400 align:middle line:10%
This experiment consisted
of stretching a membrane

00:03:35.400 --> 00:03:39.750 align:middle line:10%
across the open top of the
sarcophagus, this granite box.

00:03:39.750 --> 00:03:42.750 align:middle line:84%
And in the bottom of the
granite box, this time,

00:03:42.750 --> 00:03:44.460 align:middle line:90%
I had a small loudspeaker.

00:03:44.460 --> 00:03:46.620 align:middle line:84%
Sprinkling sand
onto the membrane

00:03:46.620 --> 00:03:49.260 align:middle line:84%
itself would create
the cymatics experiment

00:03:49.260 --> 00:03:50.700 align:middle line:90%
that I wanted to conduct.

00:03:50.700 --> 00:03:54.830 align:middle line:84%
Cymatics is the science
of sound made visible.

00:03:54.830 --> 00:03:56.990 align:middle line:84%
We switched on the
electronic oscillator

00:03:56.990 --> 00:04:01.370 align:middle line:84%
and expected to see a series
of geometric patterns.

00:04:01.370 --> 00:04:03.320 align:middle line:84%
Up to that point in
my career, that's

00:04:03.320 --> 00:04:06.140 align:middle line:84%
all I had ever seen-- just
simple geometric patterns.

00:04:06.140 --> 00:04:08.830 align:middle line:90%


00:04:08.830 --> 00:04:11.170 align:middle line:84%
What happened was
that a whole series

00:04:11.170 --> 00:04:15.685 align:middle line:84%
of ancient Egyptian hieroglyphs
began to emerge in the sand.

00:04:15.685 --> 00:04:20.040 align:middle line:90%


00:04:20.040 --> 00:04:23.280 align:middle line:10%
I actually had no idea,
I had no expectation

00:04:23.280 --> 00:04:27.120 align:middle line:10%
of seeing ancient Egyptian
hieroglyphs on this membrane.

00:04:27.120 --> 00:04:31.890 align:middle line:10%
But after about 20 minutes of
making sound in the sarcophagus

00:04:31.890 --> 00:04:33.930 align:middle line:10%
and taking all these
photographs and seeing

00:04:33.930 --> 00:04:37.500 align:middle line:10%
all these amazing ancient
Egyptian hieroglyphs appearing

00:04:37.500 --> 00:04:40.500 align:middle line:10%
on the membrane in
these sand patterns,

00:04:40.500 --> 00:04:44.370 align:middle line:10%
I suddenly realized that all
the pain in my lower back

00:04:44.370 --> 00:04:45.810 align:middle line:10%
had left me.

00:04:45.810 --> 00:04:48.990 align:middle line:84%
Well, in that moment,
actually, the thought

00:04:48.990 --> 00:04:51.630 align:middle line:84%
that went through my mind
was I know what this.

00:04:51.630 --> 00:04:53.280 align:middle line:90%
This is endorphins.

00:04:53.280 --> 00:04:56.790 align:middle line:84%
These are endorphins
flowing in my bloodstream.

00:04:56.790 --> 00:04:59.430 align:middle line:84%
I'm so happy seeing
these and excited

00:04:59.430 --> 00:05:02.760 align:middle line:84%
seeing these ancient
Egyptian hieroglyphs.

00:05:02.760 --> 00:05:05.700 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, well, when I
get back out of the pyramid

00:05:05.700 --> 00:05:08.980 align:middle line:84%
and get back to the hotel,
the pain will come back.

00:05:08.980 --> 00:05:11.520 align:middle line:84%
But the pain never
did come back.

00:05:11.520 --> 00:05:14.230 align:middle line:90%
So that really got my attention.

00:05:14.230 --> 00:05:16.500 align:middle line:84%
I thought, this
is extraordinary.

00:05:16.500 --> 00:05:19.050 align:middle line:84%
How could the pain
just suddenly vanish?

00:05:19.050 --> 00:05:21.700 align:middle line:84%
Remembering that I'd
been in severe pain

00:05:21.700 --> 00:05:25.000 align:middle line:84%
for up to three weeks
before going out to Egypt.

00:05:25.000 --> 00:05:28.660 align:middle line:84%
The other thing, of course, was
that the cymatics experiment

00:05:28.660 --> 00:05:31.240 align:middle line:90%
was phenomenally successful.

00:05:31.240 --> 00:05:35.290 align:middle line:84%
Seeing ancient Egyptian
hieroglyphs appear in sand

00:05:35.290 --> 00:05:38.020 align:middle line:84%
on a membrane in
the King's Chamber,

00:05:38.020 --> 00:05:39.850 align:middle line:84%
I mean, who would
have thought it?

00:05:39.850 --> 00:05:42.730 align:middle line:84%
I certainly didn't
expect that at all.

00:05:42.730 --> 00:05:45.490 align:middle line:90%
This seemed to be designed.

00:05:45.490 --> 00:05:48.430 align:middle line:84%
This didn't seem to
me to be happenstance.

00:05:48.430 --> 00:05:51.280 align:middle line:84%
I thought that somehow,
for some reason,

00:05:51.280 --> 00:05:55.480 align:middle line:84%
the ancient Egyptians had
decided to create this effect.

00:05:55.480 --> 00:05:58.190 align:middle line:90%


00:05:58.190 --> 00:06:01.760 align:middle line:10%
>> What we're realizing now as
cosmologists and as scientists

00:06:01.760 --> 00:06:05.360 align:middle line:10%
across many fields of research
is coming to stand alongside

00:06:05.360 --> 00:06:08.930 align:middle line:10%
these ancient spiritual
understandings.

00:06:08.930 --> 00:06:11.510 align:middle line:10%
That actually the
energy and matter

00:06:11.510 --> 00:06:14.120 align:middle line:10%
and space and time
of our universe

00:06:14.120 --> 00:06:17.840 align:middle line:10%
are expressions of
a deeper reality.

00:06:17.840 --> 00:06:20.610 align:middle line:84%
So they are the appearance
of our universe,

00:06:20.610 --> 00:06:23.480 align:middle line:84%
but they're not its
foundational truth.

00:06:23.480 --> 00:06:26.330 align:middle line:84%
And its foundational
truth is that our universe

00:06:26.330 --> 00:06:31.370 align:middle line:84%
emerges from realms of
essentially cosmic causation,

00:06:31.370 --> 00:06:32.690 align:middle line:90%
intention.

00:06:32.690 --> 00:06:37.760 align:middle line:84%
So our universe has meaning
and purpose and a journey.

00:06:37.760 --> 00:06:39.503 align:middle line:90%
The ancients were very smart.

00:06:39.503 --> 00:06:41.420 align:middle line:84%
I mean, they were at
least as smart as we are,

00:06:41.420 --> 00:06:44.690 align:middle line:90%
they just had less stuff.

00:06:44.690 --> 00:06:48.440 align:middle line:10%
>> These ancient cultures
who weren't so distracted

00:06:48.440 --> 00:06:53.030 align:middle line:10%
by developing new inventions
and all the stuff that we love

00:06:53.030 --> 00:06:56.370 align:middle line:10%
and do all the time, what
was it that they had that we

00:06:56.370 --> 00:06:57.170 align:middle line:10%
don't have?

00:06:57.170 --> 00:07:01.260 align:middle line:84%
And what has been lost as
we've gained what we've got?

00:07:01.260 --> 00:07:05.310 align:middle line:90%


00:07:05.310 --> 00:07:10.320 align:middle line:10%
>> I came to Mexico the first
time in 1979 to Chichén Itzá,

00:07:10.320 --> 00:07:14.160 align:middle line:10%
which is a World Heritage
Site with two or three million

00:07:14.160 --> 00:07:17.910 align:middle line:10%
people every year visiting,
and was stunned to see that

00:07:17.910 --> 00:07:22.080 align:middle line:10%
their main pyramid was
dedicated to a snake.

00:07:22.080 --> 00:07:23.865 align:middle line:84%
I mean, what's
that, you might say.

00:07:23.865 --> 00:07:26.040 align:middle line:84%
And then, of course,
I learned later

00:07:26.040 --> 00:07:30.150 align:middle line:84%
that the mighty city of
Teotihuacán outside of Mexico

00:07:30.150 --> 00:07:34.470 align:middle line:84%
City, its central pyramid
is devoted to Quetzalcoatl,

00:07:34.470 --> 00:07:35.640 align:middle line:90%
the plumed serpent.

00:07:35.640 --> 00:07:38.370 align:middle line:84%
Then you can go around the
world, the biblical story

00:07:38.370 --> 00:07:42.180 align:middle line:84%
about the serpent, the
Aborigines in Australia,

00:07:42.180 --> 00:07:46.920 align:middle line:84%
they worshipped a Rainbow
Serpent as their creator God.

00:07:46.920 --> 00:07:50.790 align:middle line:84%
In China, serpentine
dragons were the big thing

00:07:50.790 --> 00:07:52.990 align:middle line:90%
in divine matters, so to speak.

00:07:52.990 --> 00:07:56.160 align:middle line:84%
People all over the world
would look upon serpents

00:07:56.160 --> 00:07:59.940 align:middle line:84%
as being the creator
gods, or dragons maybe.

00:07:59.940 --> 00:08:02.100 align:middle line:84%
So it's clear,
there's something here

00:08:02.100 --> 00:08:06.000 align:middle line:84%
modern people have lost
their contact with.

00:08:06.000 --> 00:08:09.690 align:middle line:84%
Our state of consciousness is
completely different from what

00:08:09.690 --> 00:08:13.500 align:middle line:84%
it was 1,000, 2,000 years
ago, and even more so

00:08:13.500 --> 00:08:15.780 align:middle line:90%
if you go back 50,000 years ago.

00:08:15.780 --> 00:08:19.260 align:middle line:84%
And what that means is that
in the state of consciousness,

00:08:19.260 --> 00:08:22.840 align:middle line:84%
they, as well as all our
ancient people saw that.

00:08:22.840 --> 00:08:25.200 align:middle line:84%
Of course, there are
serpents and dragons,

00:08:25.200 --> 00:08:29.820 align:middle line:84%
they were living in a world of
spirits that most of us cannot

00:08:29.820 --> 00:08:33.690 align:middle line:84%
see in our current default
state of consciousness.

00:08:33.690 --> 00:08:36.690 align:middle line:84%
But in their default
state of consciousness,

00:08:36.690 --> 00:08:39.960 align:middle line:84%
it was possible to see
it and experience it.

00:08:39.960 --> 00:08:45.270 align:middle line:84%
That means that they had access
to a domain of experience

00:08:45.270 --> 00:08:50.910 align:middle line:84%
that, for the most part,
we don't have anymore.

00:08:50.910 --> 00:08:54.030 align:middle line:84%
Shamanic peoples, and I
would say Indigenous peoples

00:08:54.030 --> 00:08:58.710 align:middle line:84%
in general, they look upon
reality as multi-dimensional.

00:08:58.710 --> 00:09:01.110 align:middle line:84%
In the default state
of modern people,

00:09:01.110 --> 00:09:04.990 align:middle line:84%
it's just a rational
physical reality around them,

00:09:04.990 --> 00:09:06.270 align:middle line:90%
so to speak.

00:09:06.270 --> 00:09:09.390 align:middle line:84%
A spiritual experience
is about seeing

00:09:09.390 --> 00:09:13.040 align:middle line:84%
things that are outside
of our physical reality.

00:09:13.040 --> 00:09:16.790 align:middle line:90%


00:09:16.790 --> 00:09:19.250 align:middle line:90%
>> Where do I go when I die?

00:09:19.250 --> 00:09:21.060 align:middle line:90%
It's such a beautiful question.

00:09:21.060 --> 00:09:25.580 align:middle line:84%
And one of the answers
is, that you don't.

00:09:25.580 --> 00:09:29.030 align:middle line:84%
Your body goes in the
ground, we understand that.

00:09:29.030 --> 00:09:32.810 align:middle line:84%
Your personality diffuses in
whatever way that it does.

00:09:32.810 --> 00:09:36.810 align:middle line:90%
But you are already everywhere.

00:09:36.810 --> 00:09:41.400 align:middle line:84%
So how is it that you think
you're going to go somewhere?

00:09:41.400 --> 00:09:45.640 align:middle line:90%
You've always been there.

00:09:45.640 --> 00:09:49.630 align:middle line:10%
>> People seem to be more
concerned about what it takes

00:09:49.630 --> 00:09:53.770 align:middle line:10%
on the way to death, what
the experience might be,

00:09:53.770 --> 00:09:55.240 align:middle line:10%
how you die.

00:09:55.240 --> 00:09:58.220 align:middle line:10%
So not necessarily
what comes after it,

00:09:58.220 --> 00:10:00.190 align:middle line:10%
but what leads up to it.

00:10:00.190 --> 00:10:03.610 align:middle line:84%
Long illnesses
and how might that

00:10:03.610 --> 00:10:06.500 align:middle line:84%
be more difficult than
dying all at once,

00:10:06.500 --> 00:10:08.590 align:middle line:84%
let's say, or dropping
dead of a heart attack.

00:10:08.590 --> 00:10:12.580 align:middle line:84%
And, is one way of dying better
than another way of dying?

00:10:12.580 --> 00:10:15.070 align:middle line:84%
And the spirits will
even bring this up.

00:10:15.070 --> 00:10:21.550 align:middle line:84%
They will discuss the experience
of what leads up to death.

00:10:21.550 --> 00:10:26.410 align:middle line:84%
How someone demonstrated their
love by caring for a person?

00:10:26.410 --> 00:10:29.320 align:middle line:84%
What were the conversations
that were had?

00:10:29.320 --> 00:10:32.770 align:middle line:84%
We have such issues
around dying.

00:10:32.770 --> 00:10:36.760 align:middle line:84%
It seems that that's where the
issues are, not around death

00:10:36.760 --> 00:10:37.750 align:middle line:90%
itself as much.

00:10:37.750 --> 00:10:42.180 align:middle line:90%


00:10:42.180 --> 00:10:45.630 align:middle line:84%
We think that we
are losing people.

00:10:45.630 --> 00:10:49.950 align:middle line:84%
We think that there is no
way back to the relationship.

00:10:49.950 --> 00:10:51.750 align:middle line:90%
That the relationship is lost.

00:10:51.750 --> 00:10:53.580 align:middle line:90%
The communication is lost.

00:10:53.580 --> 00:10:57.480 align:middle line:84%
The physicality of
that person is lost.

00:10:57.480 --> 00:11:00.690 align:middle line:84%
What I have learned over
time is the physicality

00:11:00.690 --> 00:11:04.510 align:middle line:84%
is even part of our
spirit relationship.

00:11:04.510 --> 00:11:07.950 align:middle line:84%
So the spirits will
still have an effect

00:11:07.950 --> 00:11:11.010 align:middle line:84%
here in the physical world
because after all, they

00:11:11.010 --> 00:11:11.910 align:middle line:90%
are energy.

00:11:11.910 --> 00:11:15.160 align:middle line:84%
And energy changes form,
but it doesn't disappear,

00:11:15.160 --> 00:11:16.260 align:middle line:90%
it isn't created.

00:11:16.260 --> 00:11:21.300 align:middle line:10%
And so in this way, things
in our life can move.

00:11:21.300 --> 00:11:22.960 align:middle line:90%
We can be inspired.

00:11:22.960 --> 00:11:25.260 align:middle line:84%
There can be
continued connection

00:11:25.260 --> 00:11:27.240 align:middle line:90%
with those who have passed.

00:11:27.240 --> 00:11:30.300 align:middle line:84%
>> My mother passed a
few years before my dad.

00:11:30.300 --> 00:11:32.760 align:middle line:84%
And one day, I
woke up from sleep.

00:11:32.760 --> 00:11:37.690 align:middle line:10%
And clear as AT&T can make
it, my mom's voice said,

00:11:37.690 --> 00:11:39.880 align:middle line:10%
your dad's going to die
soon and it's no big deal.

00:11:39.880 --> 00:11:41.350 align:middle line:90%
And he died soon.

00:11:41.350 --> 00:11:44.240 align:middle line:84%
So she's giving me
a little heads up.

00:11:44.240 --> 00:11:47.720 align:middle line:84%
All the senses can be involved
rather than they hear a voice.

00:11:47.720 --> 00:11:50.900 align:middle line:84%
Like telepathically, when
my grandfather comes to me--

00:11:50.900 --> 00:11:52.790 align:middle line:90%
he's been long gone--

00:11:52.790 --> 00:11:55.160 align:middle line:84%
I smell Captain
Black pipe tobacco.

00:11:55.160 --> 00:11:57.440 align:middle line:84%
Some people, their
grandmother's cookies.

00:11:57.440 --> 00:12:00.230 align:middle line:84%
>> When I was speaking to
a group of college students

00:12:00.230 --> 00:12:05.690 align:middle line:84%
and giving messages, the
physicist Niels Bohr showed up

00:12:05.690 --> 00:12:10.280 align:middle line:84%
next to a young man who didn't
believe in this work at all.

00:12:10.280 --> 00:12:17.180 align:middle line:84%
He was gobsmacked because he was
writing a paper on Niels Bohr's

00:12:17.180 --> 00:12:22.730 align:middle line:84%
work and how it could be
furthered on this planet now.

00:12:22.730 --> 00:12:25.820 align:middle line:10%
There was a musician
who came to see me,

00:12:25.820 --> 00:12:29.450 align:middle line:10%
and Woody Guthrie showed up
with her-- surprise, surprise.

00:12:29.450 --> 00:12:33.650 align:middle line:84%
Well, it turns out she was
doing her first concert outdoors

00:12:33.650 --> 00:12:35.360 align:middle line:90%
and it was Woody Guthrie music.

00:12:35.360 --> 00:12:37.700 align:middle line:90%
And he was there inspiring her.

00:12:37.700 --> 00:12:41.990 align:middle line:10%
Spirits we do not personally
know but may be connected

00:12:41.990 --> 00:12:46.560 align:middle line:10%
through their work or a through
line of what they started here

00:12:46.560 --> 00:12:49.080 align:middle line:10%
on this planet,
we can be inspired

00:12:49.080 --> 00:12:50.835 align:middle line:10%
and we can be helped
by them as well.

00:12:50.835 --> 00:12:53.380 align:middle line:90%


00:12:53.380 --> 00:12:55.810 align:middle line:84%
When we die, we
do not die alone.

00:12:55.810 --> 00:12:58.430 align:middle line:84%
Which is very important
for people to know,

00:12:58.430 --> 00:13:00.670 align:middle line:84%
especially if they can't
be with a loved one.

00:13:00.670 --> 00:13:03.310 align:middle line:84%
Those in spirit who
have gone before

00:13:03.310 --> 00:13:06.760 align:middle line:84%
are actually present with
the person who is dying.

00:13:06.760 --> 00:13:09.190 align:middle line:84%
No matter how quickly
that person may die,

00:13:09.190 --> 00:13:12.250 align:middle line:84%
no matter how tragically,
no matter how suddenly,

00:13:12.250 --> 00:13:14.440 align:middle line:90%
no matter how traumatically.

00:13:14.440 --> 00:13:20.680 align:middle line:84%
There is a group that is present
helping that person to pass.

00:13:20.680 --> 00:13:26.440 align:middle line:84%
Now in some dramatic
situations, two young children

00:13:26.440 --> 00:13:30.850 align:middle line:84%
