00:34:48.690 --> 00:34:50.860 align:middle line:10%
through space and time.

00:34:50.860 --> 00:34:53.219 align:middle line:10%
The time part is sometimes
called precognition.

00:34:53.219 --> 00:34:57.480 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes you see backwards in
time, so that's retrocognition.

00:34:57.480 --> 00:35:00.540 align:middle line:84%
This kind of experience
is you go to a place

00:35:00.540 --> 00:35:04.740 align:middle line:84%
and you see people in
period costumes apparently

00:35:04.740 --> 00:35:06.090 align:middle line:90%
and everything looks old.

00:35:06.090 --> 00:35:07.960 align:middle line:84%
You're wondering,
what's happening here?

00:35:07.960 --> 00:35:11.760 align:middle line:84%
Well, it's like a retro
cognitive sense of the place,

00:35:11.760 --> 00:35:15.110 align:middle line:90%
but sometime in the past.

00:35:15.110 --> 00:35:19.377 align:middle line:84%
>> Precognition is, in my
view, a human birthright.

00:35:19.377 --> 00:35:20.960 align:middle line:84%
And actually, I think
there's evidence

00:35:20.960 --> 00:35:22.340 align:middle line:90%
that other animals have it.

00:35:22.340 --> 00:35:25.760 align:middle line:10%
But certainly among humans,
I think everyone has it.

00:35:25.760 --> 00:35:28.070 align:middle line:10%
And the question is, can
you get conscious of it,

00:35:28.070 --> 00:35:31.770 align:middle line:10%
and what's your skill level
with communicating it to others?

00:35:31.770 --> 00:35:33.140 align:middle line:90%
And so you can learn that.

00:35:33.140 --> 00:35:34.730 align:middle line:84%
You can learn to
get conscious of it,

00:35:34.730 --> 00:35:36.740 align:middle line:84%
and you can learn to
communicate it to others.

00:35:36.740 --> 00:35:38.240 align:middle line:84%
It's very much like
musical ability.

00:35:38.240 --> 00:35:40.130 align:middle line:84%
I don't think it's that hard
to teach most people how

00:35:40.130 --> 00:35:41.845 align:middle line:84%
to hum a simple tune,
which is, I think,

00:35:41.845 --> 00:35:43.220 align:middle line:84%
the equivalent of
teaching people

00:35:43.220 --> 00:35:44.637 align:middle line:84%
how to do controlled
precognition.

00:35:44.637 --> 00:35:45.800 align:middle line:90%
Most people can do it.

00:35:45.800 --> 00:35:48.383 align:middle line:84%
And they're actually impressed
with themselves when they do it

00:35:48.383 --> 00:35:50.960 align:middle line:84%
because we don't usually think
we can predict the future.

00:35:50.960 --> 00:35:53.810 align:middle line:84%
But to get to the level of skill
that it's operational and can

00:35:53.810 --> 00:35:59.120 align:middle line:84%
be used, like to become an opera
singer or the first violinist

00:35:59.120 --> 00:36:02.480 align:middle line:84%
in a symphony orchestra, there's
a lot of practice involved.

00:36:02.480 --> 00:36:04.400 align:middle line:84%
And you probably wouldn't
practice that much

00:36:04.400 --> 00:36:08.180 align:middle line:84%
if you didn't have
that initial talent.

00:36:08.180 --> 00:36:13.490 align:middle line:10%
>> I was a returning student
living in the Chicago area.

00:36:13.490 --> 00:36:16.650 align:middle line:84%
After taking several years
off to get married and have

00:36:16.650 --> 00:36:20.970 align:middle line:84%
kids and all that thing, I had
recently come across a paper

00:36:20.970 --> 00:36:23.130 align:middle line:84%
that Hal Puthoff
and Russell Targ

00:36:23.130 --> 00:36:25.890 align:middle line:84%
had published about their
remote viewing work.

00:36:25.890 --> 00:36:29.730 align:middle line:10%
They mentioned in the paper
that sometimes the percipient

00:36:29.730 --> 00:36:33.240 align:middle line:10%
could describe the scene
before it was selected.

00:36:33.240 --> 00:36:35.320 align:middle line:10%
And I came up short on that.

00:36:35.320 --> 00:36:38.700 align:middle line:84%
I said, the distance
part doesn't bother me,

00:36:38.700 --> 00:36:40.980 align:middle line:90%
but the time part, I don't know.

00:36:40.980 --> 00:36:42.890 align:middle line:90%
That's really hard to swallow.

00:36:42.890 --> 00:36:46.230 align:middle line:10%
>> And when we study
intuition in a science form,

00:36:46.230 --> 00:36:50.130 align:middle line:10%
often we'll call it remote
viewing because there,

00:36:50.130 --> 00:36:54.030 align:middle line:10%
the person has no way to
know the information except

00:36:54.030 --> 00:36:55.050 align:middle line:10%
for psychically.

00:36:55.050 --> 00:36:59.160 align:middle line:84%
>> So there I was, a suburban
housewife on a Sunday afternoon

00:36:59.160 --> 00:37:00.720 align:middle line:90%
folding laundry.

00:37:00.720 --> 00:37:02.430 align:middle line:90%
And I'm thinking about this.

00:37:02.430 --> 00:37:04.770 align:middle line:84%
And I'm thinking
about it and I said,

00:37:04.770 --> 00:37:07.470 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to just think
about a friend of mine

00:37:07.470 --> 00:37:10.110 align:middle line:84%
and see if I can figure
out where she's going

00:37:10.110 --> 00:37:12.510 align:middle line:90%
to be at 5:30 this evening.

00:37:12.510 --> 00:37:16.720 align:middle line:84%
And then I'll call her tonight
and find out where she was.

00:37:16.720 --> 00:37:20.500 align:middle line:84%
The thought had no
sooner hit me than I

00:37:20.500 --> 00:37:23.140 align:middle line:84%
had this image or this
feeling of her walking

00:37:23.140 --> 00:37:25.600 align:middle line:84%
in the woods, which
was not something

00:37:25.600 --> 00:37:26.920 align:middle line:90%
that was typical for her.

00:37:26.920 --> 00:37:30.110 align:middle line:84%
She would have been bike riding
or playing tennis or something.

00:37:30.110 --> 00:37:32.500 align:middle line:84%
And I said, OK, I'll
just call her later

00:37:32.500 --> 00:37:34.600 align:middle line:90%
and see where she was at 5:30.

00:37:34.600 --> 00:37:37.420 align:middle line:84%
This was at about
4:00 o'clock or 4:30.

00:37:37.420 --> 00:37:42.040 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, 5:20 or so comes,
the doorbell rings.

00:37:42.040 --> 00:37:45.070 align:middle line:84%
There's my friend standing
outside and saying,

00:37:45.070 --> 00:37:46.870 align:middle line:84%
I've been going
stir crazy and I was

00:37:46.870 --> 00:37:49.420 align:middle line:84%
thinking it would be nice to
go take a walk in the woods.

00:37:49.420 --> 00:37:51.550 align:middle line:90%
Would you like to come?

00:37:51.550 --> 00:37:56.440 align:middle line:84%
And after I picked my
chin up off the floor,

00:37:56.440 --> 00:37:59.930 align:middle line:90%
I was just blown away.

00:37:59.930 --> 00:38:02.680 align:middle line:90%
I decided this was too much.

00:38:02.680 --> 00:38:04.870 align:middle line:90%
I had to explore it.

00:38:04.870 --> 00:38:10.540 align:middle line:10%
>> I created a protocol, for
what I call distant viewing

00:38:10.540 --> 00:38:14.500 align:middle line:10%
in those days, in my back garden
of this house that I was in.

00:38:14.500 --> 00:38:18.400 align:middle line:84%
I laid out a grid
that was 12 squares.

00:38:18.400 --> 00:38:22.420 align:middle line:84%
And I would take mason
jars and put things in them

00:38:22.420 --> 00:38:25.180 align:middle line:90%
and bury them in this grid.

00:38:25.180 --> 00:38:28.720 align:middle line:90%
I had a mimeograph paper--

00:38:28.720 --> 00:38:31.270 align:middle line:84%
that's how old this
was, mimeographs--

00:38:31.270 --> 00:38:33.010 align:middle line:90%
that was just the grid.

00:38:33.010 --> 00:38:35.630 align:middle line:84%
And I would send it
out to people and say,

00:38:35.630 --> 00:38:40.180 align:middle line:84%
can you try to locate
which square in the grid

00:38:40.180 --> 00:38:43.090 align:middle line:84%
has something buried
there, and can you

00:38:43.090 --> 00:38:46.000 align:middle line:90%
describe for me what it is.

00:38:46.000 --> 00:38:48.340 align:middle line:84%
And I discovered that
people could do it.

00:38:48.340 --> 00:38:51.490 align:middle line:84%
>> A computer may pick a
target that no human has seen

00:38:51.490 --> 00:38:54.820 align:middle line:84%
in California, and the remote
viewer may be in Virginia.

00:38:54.820 --> 00:38:57.820 align:middle line:84%
They will draw that target
out with such precision

00:38:57.820 --> 00:39:03.100 align:middle line:84%
that if you wanted to know, say,
the target was a dish, where

00:39:03.100 --> 00:39:06.880 align:middle line:84%
the dish was made and
how many kids the person

00:39:06.880 --> 00:39:09.640 align:middle line:84%
who packed the dish
into the container had,

00:39:09.640 --> 00:39:11.560 align:middle line:84%
you could find that
information out.

00:39:11.560 --> 00:39:14.980 align:middle line:84%
So you can access all
information without regard

00:39:14.980 --> 00:39:16.000 align:middle line:90%
to time or space.

00:39:16.000 --> 00:39:19.360 align:middle line:84%
You can go forward in the
future, back in the past.

00:39:19.360 --> 00:39:23.500 align:middle line:84%
>> Most of the researchers who
do this kind of work start out

00:39:23.500 --> 00:39:25.450 align:middle line:90%
with, is this stuff real?

00:39:25.450 --> 00:39:31.090 align:middle line:84%
My question was, what can you
do with it of practical utility,

00:39:31.090 --> 00:39:34.900 align:middle line:84%
how can you do that, and
what is it telling us

00:39:34.900 --> 00:39:39.550 align:middle line:84%
about who we are as human beings
and our place in the universe?

00:39:39.550 --> 00:39:42.490 align:middle line:84%
There was a huge
discussion at that time.

00:39:42.490 --> 00:39:45.580 align:middle line:84%
Most archeological finds
were made serendipitously.

00:39:45.580 --> 00:39:48.610 align:middle line:84%
They were doing road work
and they revealed a temple,

00:39:48.610 --> 00:39:52.000 align:middle line:84%
or some farmer was
plowing in a field

00:39:52.000 --> 00:39:54.250 align:middle line:90%
and found a burial or whatever.

00:39:54.250 --> 00:39:58.540 align:middle line:84%
We used this protocol that I had
designed in Alexandria, Egypt

00:39:58.540 --> 00:40:01.960 align:middle line:84%
to locate the
Palace of Cleopatra,

00:40:01.960 --> 00:40:04.990 align:middle line:84%
the Palace of Mark
Antony, the Timonium,

00:40:04.990 --> 00:40:07.450 align:middle line:84%
the Lighthouse of
Pharos, one of the seven

00:40:07.450 --> 00:40:09.070 align:middle line:90%
wonders of the ancient world.

00:40:09.070 --> 00:40:10.060 align:middle line:90%
You can see this.

00:40:10.060 --> 00:40:12.380 align:middle line:84%
It's upon YouTube, The
Alexandria Project.

00:40:12.380 --> 00:40:13.180 align:middle line:90%
You can find it.

00:40:13.180 --> 00:40:14.230 align:middle line:90%
Watch it happen.

00:40:14.230 --> 00:40:16.630 align:middle line:10%
>> Our remote viewer
here, Joe McMoneagle,

00:40:16.630 --> 00:40:20.000 align:middle line:10%
has found ancient temple sites
in Japan that nobody knew

00:40:20.000 --> 00:40:20.800 align:middle line:10%
about.

00:40:20.800 --> 00:40:22.175 align:middle line:84%
He has worked with
the government

00:40:22.175 --> 00:40:25.000 align:middle line:84%
for 20 years in their
program, and could draw,

00:40:25.000 --> 00:40:28.990 align:middle line:84%
in high detail, the inside of
a new submarine the Soviets had

00:40:28.990 --> 00:40:30.220 align:middle line:90%
before it was ever launched.

00:40:30.220 --> 00:40:33.130 align:middle line:10%
>> I wouldn't do
classified research.

00:40:33.130 --> 00:40:36.250 align:middle line:10%
I felt that anything we
knew about consciousness,

00:40:36.250 --> 00:40:38.680 align:middle line:10%
given the state of
humanity, we ought

00:40:38.680 --> 00:40:42.040 align:middle line:10%
to make immediately available.

00:40:42.040 --> 00:40:46.910 align:middle line:84%
>> Could remote viewers locate
an unknown shipwreck on the sea

00:40:46.910 --> 00:40:47.710 align:middle line:90%
floor?

00:40:47.710 --> 00:40:52.240 align:middle line:84%
That is, could they look through
hundreds of feet of seawater

00:40:52.240 --> 00:40:55.900 align:middle line:84%
and locate a previously
unknown wreck on the sea floor?

00:40:55.900 --> 00:41:00.290 align:middle line:84%
So I got a chart and I
sent it out to 11 people.

00:41:00.290 --> 00:41:03.190 align:middle line:84%
And I said to them,
please go over this chart

00:41:03.190 --> 00:41:05.110 align:middle line:90%
and locate an unknown sea wreck.

00:41:05.110 --> 00:41:07.840 align:middle line:84%
That came to be known
as Project Deep Quest.

00:41:07.840 --> 00:41:10.270 align:middle line:84%
I filmed it also,
it's up on YouTube.

00:41:10.270 --> 00:41:12.430 align:middle line:84%
I got Leonard Nimoy
to narrate it.

00:41:12.430 --> 00:41:17.350 align:middle line:84%
>> We are dancing with parts
greater than ourselves that we

00:41:17.350 --> 00:41:18.670 align:middle line:90%
don't fully understand.

00:41:18.670 --> 00:41:23.020 align:middle line:84%
That may be our higher self,
it may be guides and angels,

00:41:23.020 --> 00:41:26.650 align:middle line:84%
it may be God, it
may be all kinds

00:41:26.650 --> 00:41:31.030 align:middle line:84%
of things that were accessing
beyond our personality and ego.

00:41:31.030 --> 00:41:33.220 align:middle line:10%
>> Precognition in remote
viewing are related

00:41:33.220 --> 00:41:38.060 align:middle line:10%
in the sense that precognition
is a larger umbrella term that

00:41:38.060 --> 00:41:42.290 align:middle line:10%
includes multiple ways in which
you could be precognitive.

00:41:42.290 --> 00:41:45.287 align:middle line:84%
So one way is
physiologically, your body

00:41:45.287 --> 00:41:47.870 align:middle line:84%
can predict future events that
you don't even consciously know

00:41:47.870 --> 00:41:48.710 align:middle line:90%
it's predicting.

00:41:48.710 --> 00:41:51.048 align:middle line:84%
Before an important
event occurs,

00:41:51.048 --> 00:41:53.090 align:middle line:84%
you might have had the
experience of a zing going

00:41:53.090 --> 00:41:55.370 align:middle line:84%
through your body, like,
wait, something's going on.

00:41:55.370 --> 00:41:58.970 align:middle line:84%
>> They did a study based on
a factor called interoception.

00:41:58.970 --> 00:42:01.610 align:middle line:10%
That's when you're able
to sense your heartbeat

00:42:01.610 --> 00:42:03.530 align:middle line:10%
or sense your viscera.

00:42:03.530 --> 00:42:05.690 align:middle line:10%
Some people are
very good at that.

00:42:05.690 --> 00:42:09.020 align:middle line:10%
For reasons I don't understand,
I can just sit down and be calm

00:42:09.020 --> 00:42:11.420 align:middle line:10%
and I can feel my
heartbeat all the time.

00:42:11.420 --> 00:42:12.930 align:middle line:90%
Well, other people can't.

00:42:12.930 --> 00:42:15.750 align:middle line:84%
So people who are good
at that tend to do much,

00:42:15.750 --> 00:42:19.160 align:middle line:84%
much better in terms of day
trading with futures than ones

00:42:19.160 --> 00:42:20.100 align:middle line:90%
who don't.

00:42:20.100 --> 00:42:22.400 align:middle line:84%
And so you can learn
to pay attention

00:42:22.400 --> 00:42:25.400 align:middle line:84%
to these what amounts to
signals coming from your body.

00:42:25.400 --> 00:42:27.920 align:middle line:84%
And, yeah, you could
get better at it.

00:42:27.920 --> 00:42:31.070 align:middle line:84%
One of the common ones is
you're driving to work one day

00:42:31.070 --> 00:42:32.570 align:middle line:84%
and you're reaching
an intersection.

00:42:32.570 --> 00:42:33.987 align:middle line:84%
You have a green
light, everything

00:42:33.987 --> 00:42:35.210 align:middle line:90%
seems to be working fine.

00:42:35.210 --> 00:42:37.850 align:middle line:84%
You have an internal sense that
something's not quite right

00:42:37.850 --> 00:42:39.313 align:middle line:90%
so you start slowing down.

00:42:39.313 --> 00:42:40.730 align:middle line:84%
And people behind
you are thinking

00:42:40.730 --> 00:42:42.320 align:middle line:90%
what is wrong with you.

00:42:42.320 --> 00:42:43.580 align:middle line:90%
So you slow down, slow down.

00:42:43.580 --> 00:42:47.000 align:middle line:84%
You still have a green light
and you're going really slow,

00:42:47.000 --> 00:42:49.220 align:middle line:84%
and suddenly somebody
shoots through the red light

00:42:49.220 --> 00:42:52.100 align:middle line:84%
and would have hit you broadside
if you didn't slow down.

00:42:52.100 --> 00:42:55.310 align:middle line:84%
Maybe that suggests that his
peripheral vision, maybe you

00:42:55.310 --> 00:42:57.500 align:middle line:84%
saw something you didn't
even realize you saw it.

00:42:57.500 --> 00:43:01.160 align:middle line:84%
But maybe also you
had a premonition

00:43:01.160 --> 00:43:02.788 align:middle line:84%
that something bad
was about to happen.

00:43:02.788 --> 00:43:04.580 align:middle line:84%
And so you didn't know
exactly what it was,

00:43:04.580 --> 00:43:06.200 align:middle line:90%
but you just slowed down anyway.

00:43:06.200 --> 00:43:08.960 align:middle line:84%
So we take that into the
laboratory into an experiment

00:43:08.960 --> 00:43:11.870 align:middle line:84%
we call presentiment,
which is not precognition.

00:43:11.870 --> 00:43:14.415 align:middle line:84%
It's not pre-knowing,
but it's pre-feeling.

00:43:14.415 --> 00:43:16.040 align:middle line:84%
Since it's not
something that you know,

00:43:16.040 --> 00:43:19.430 align:middle line:84%
we have to use your body
as an indicator of what's

00:43:19.430 --> 00:43:20.240 align:middle line:90%
about to happen.

00:43:20.240 --> 00:43:22.640 align:middle line:84%
We measure your heart rate
or your skin conductance

00:43:22.640 --> 00:43:25.400 align:middle line:84%
or your pupil dilation
or your brainwaves.

00:43:25.400 --> 00:43:27.500 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes we measure all
of them at the same time.

00:43:27.500 --> 00:43:30.000 align:middle line:84%
>> Having someone in the room
that knows what the target is,

00:43:30.000 --> 00:43:33.590 align:middle line:84%
is going to make you
potentially tune in to what

00:43:33.590 --> 00:43:37.070 align:middle line:84%
they're thinking about
instead of the actual event.

00:43:37.070 --> 00:43:39.470 align:middle line:84%
You can use a random number
generator to produce events,

00:43:39.470 --> 00:43:43.010 align:middle line:84%
like showing a picture of a
plane crash versus a picture

00:43:43.010 --> 00:43:44.687 align:middle line:90%
of a pair of shoes.

00:43:44.687 --> 00:43:45.770 align:middle line:90%
So something more neutral.

00:43:45.770 --> 00:43:47.570 align:middle line:84%
No one on the planet
knows what the target is,

00:43:47.570 --> 00:43:49.278 align:middle line:84%
and then you can
actually get information

00:43:49.278 --> 00:43:51.590 align:middle line:84%
that you know is free
of anyone else's bias.

00:43:51.590 --> 00:43:54.980 align:middle line:84%
>> If, in fact, you're feeling
your future physiological

00:43:54.980 --> 00:43:57.500 align:middle line:84%
state, maybe that you
feel something in your gut

00:43:57.500 --> 00:43:59.120 align:middle line:90%
that's not quite right.

00:43:59.120 --> 00:44:03.860 align:middle line:84%
Then before you see one of these
negative or emotional pictures,

00:44:03.860 --> 00:44:07.070 align:middle line:84%
maybe the body begins to
become more emotional even

00:44:07.070 --> 00:44:10.200 align:middle line:84%
though, in this case, there's no
peripheral information at all.

00:44:10.200 --> 00:44:12.560 align:middle line:84%
It has to come from the
future because nobody

00:44:12.560 --> 00:44:14.840 align:middle line:84%
knows in advance
what's about to show up

00:44:14.840 --> 00:44:16.680 align:middle line:90%
by the design of the experiment.

00:44:16.680 --> 00:44:19.190 align:middle line:84%
So this experiment has been
done many, many times now.

00:44:19.190 --> 00:44:21.770 align:middle line:84%
>> You can see beforehand,
when you analyze the data,

00:44:21.770 --> 00:44:24.170 align:middle line:84%
the difference between
the physiology leading up

00:44:24.170 --> 00:44:26.600 align:middle line:84%
to the randomly selected
emotional image versus

00:44:26.600 --> 00:44:28.730 align:middle line:84%
the randomly selected
neutral image.

00:44:28.730 --> 00:44:30.950 align:middle line:84%
>> Virtually, every
physiological measure that we

00:44:30.950 --> 00:44:36.750 align:middle line:84%
look at does respond between
around 1 and 9 seconds before

00:44:36.750 --> 00:44:38.910 align:middle line:84%
the image comes up in
an appropriate way.

00:44:38.910 --> 00:44:42.690 align:middle line:84%
That's an example of taking a
relatively common experience,

00:44:42.690 --> 00:44:44.580 align:middle line:84%
putting it into a
laboratory context

00:44:44.580 --> 00:44:46.800 align:middle line:84%
where it's extremely
controlled, and that you

00:44:46.800 --> 00:44:49.740 align:middle line:84%
can exclude all of the
usual mundane explanations.

00:44:49.740 --> 00:44:51.720 align:middle line:84%
And what you're left
with is apparently

00:44:51.720 --> 00:44:55.170 align:middle line:84%
the fact that we can know
between 1 and 9 seconds

00:44:55.170 --> 00:44:57.010 align:middle line:90%
or so what is about to happen.

00:44:57.010 --> 00:45:01.050 align:middle line:10%
>> Do we look into the future,
or do we somehow or other tap

00:45:01.050 --> 00:45:05.500 align:middle line:10%
into the probabilities
of a possible future?

00:45:05.500 --> 00:45:07.450 align:middle line:90%
I don't know the answer to that.

00:45:07.450 --> 00:45:11.670 align:middle line:84%
I don't believe the future
is set and absolute.

00:45:11.670 --> 00:45:13.800 align:middle line:84%
I think, like
everything else, there's

00:45:13.800 --> 00:45:17.260 align:middle line:90%
a probabilistic aspect to it.

00:45:17.260 --> 00:45:19.560 align:middle line:10%
>> Another example is
compulsive precognition,

00:45:19.560 --> 00:45:21.660 align:middle line:10%
where you don't know why
you have to do something,

00:45:21.660 --> 00:45:23.230 align:middle line:10%
you just have to do it.

00:45:23.230 --> 00:45:24.900 align:middle line:10%
And then once you
do it, you come back

00:45:24.900 --> 00:45:27.815 align:middle line:10%
and you recognize, oh, if I had
been there during that time,

00:45:27.815 --> 00:45:29.440 align:middle line:10%
something horrible
would have happened.

00:45:29.440 --> 00:45:31.732 align:middle line:10%
There's an officer in the
military, relatively high up,

00:45:31.732 --> 00:45:34.720 align:middle line:10%
and he's in Iraq in his van.

00:45:34.720 --> 00:45:37.370 align:middle line:10%
And he was just waiting around
for the next thing to happen.

00:45:37.370 --> 00:45:38.620 align:middle line:90%
And it was really hot.

00:45:38.620 --> 00:45:41.990 align:middle line:84%
And he was sitting
on a cooler of water.

00:45:41.990 --> 00:45:46.160 align:middle line:84%
So he could absolutely have
had some water from the cooler.

00:45:46.160 --> 00:45:46.960 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:45:46.960 --> 00:45:48.130 align:middle line:90%
But that's not what he did.

00:45:48.130 --> 00:45:49.060 align:middle line:90%
He felt compelled.

00:45:49.060 --> 00:45:50.020 align:middle line:90%
He said, no, I don't want water.

00:45:50.020 --> 00:45:52.270 align:middle line:84%
I want this kind of iced tea
that I have to get up out

00:45:52.270 --> 00:45:53.123 align:middle line:90%
of here to go get.

00:45:53.123 --> 00:45:54.040 align:middle line:90%
Now that's ridiculous.

00:45:54.040 --> 00:45:55.240 align:middle line:90%
I could just have the water.

00:45:55.240 --> 00:45:56.740 align:middle line:84%
Nope, I'm going to
get the iced tea.

00:45:56.740 --> 00:46:00.190 align:middle line:84%
So he stands up, he goes and
gets the iced tea, comes back.

00:46:00.190 --> 00:46:03.850 align:middle line:84%
And he can't go back because
a mortar had landed right

00:46:03.850 --> 00:46:05.980 align:middle line:90%
near the van.

00:46:05.980 --> 00:46:08.352 align:middle line:84%
If he had been there,
he might have been right

00:46:08.352 --> 00:46:09.560 align:middle line:90%
in the way of this situation.

00:46:09.560 --> 00:46:11.875 align:middle line:84%
So that's an example of
compulsive precognition.

00:46:11.875 --> 00:46:15.910 align:middle line:84%
>> How can you explain a
phenomenon that doesn't respond

00:46:15.910 --> 00:46:17.260 align:middle line:90%
to space and time?

00:46:17.260 --> 00:46:18.670 align:middle line:90%
>> That's an anecdotal story.

00:46:18.670 --> 00:46:19.720 align:middle line:90%
That's not an experiment.

00:46:19.720 --> 00:46:23.860 align:middle line:84%
>> The only conclusion I
personally can come to is that

00:46:23.860 --> 00:46:27.490 align:middle line:84%
space and time are not
characteristics of the physical

00:46:27.490 --> 00:46:28.300 align:middle line:90%
world.

00:46:28.300 --> 00:46:31.780 align:middle line:84%
They are characteristics
of our consciousness.

00:46:31.780 --> 00:46:34.720 align:middle line:84%
Or, as Albert
Einstein once said,

00:46:34.720 --> 00:46:38.110 align:middle line:84%
they're there to keep everything
from happening all at once.

00:46:38.110 --> 00:46:41.140 align:middle line:84%
>> The basic message is time
doesn't work the way we think

00:46:41.140 --> 00:46:42.070 align:middle line:90%
it does.

00:46:42.070 --> 00:46:45.340 align:middle line:84%
And you can get
information through time

00:46:45.340 --> 00:46:48.172 align:middle line:84%
and use that information
if you're compelled to,

00:46:48.172 --> 00:46:49.630 align:middle line:84%
and if you feel
you have the talent

00:46:49.630 --> 00:46:50.925 align:middle line:90%
and you want to develop it.

00:46:50.925 --> 00:46:53.050 align:middle line:10%
>> If information is flowing
from the outside world

00:46:53.050 --> 00:46:57.550 align:middle line:10%
into you, it's somewhat passive,
this would be called the ESP.

00:46:57.550 --> 00:47:00.610 align:middle line:10%
So it's precognition
and clairvoyance.

00:47:00.610 --> 00:47:04.330 align:middle line:84%
If the information is going out
from you somehow and changing

00:47:04.330 --> 00:47:06.250 align:middle line:84%
the world, then
it's psychokinetic.

00:47:06.250 --> 00:47:09.140 align:middle line:10%
>> Most people would define
that as affecting matter with

00:47:09.140 --> 00:47:09.940 align:middle line:10%
your mind.

00:47:09.940 --> 00:47:13.120 align:middle line:84%
>> Using your intention to
change or manipulate the world

00:47:13.120 --> 00:47:14.770 align:middle line:90%
in some way outside of yourself.

00:47:14.770 --> 00:47:18.550 align:middle line:84%
>> They said explore,
experiment, expand,

00:47:18.550 --> 00:47:21.520 align:middle line:84%
play to really
widen your horizons.

00:47:21.520 --> 00:47:24.880 align:middle line:84%
We were having a time to
play with the energies

00:47:24.880 --> 00:47:26.300 align:middle line:90%
we'd been working with.

00:47:26.300 --> 00:47:28.930 align:middle line:90%
And we had a gaming night.

00:47:28.930 --> 00:47:30.700 align:middle line:90%
There were dice there.

00:47:30.700 --> 00:47:33.730 align:middle line:84%
And I found myself going
into that same energy--

00:47:33.730 --> 00:47:37.540 align:middle line:84%
wide open heart, warm hands,
connected to the Earth really

00:47:37.540 --> 00:47:40.430 align:middle line:84%
strongly, but connected
with spirit as well.

00:47:40.430 --> 00:47:43.270 align:middle line:84%
And I found I could roll
what I wanted on the dice.

00:47:43.270 --> 00:47:48.110 align:middle line:84%
OK, so seven, seven in a
row, that kind of thing.

00:47:48.110 --> 00:47:49.870 align:middle line:90%
And that's studiable.

00:47:49.870 --> 00:47:52.630 align:middle line:84%
Some of the things I'm
really interested in

00:47:52.630 --> 00:47:57.430 align:middle line:84%
is when we do PK versus rest
when there's no psychokinesis.

00:47:57.430 --> 00:47:59.180 align:middle line:90%
What's going on in the brain?

00:47:59.180 --> 00:48:02.890 align:middle line:84%
So we do a 128 lead
EEG on a person's head.

00:48:02.890 --> 00:48:06.490 align:middle line:84%
And we find real
interesting EEG results

00:48:06.490 --> 00:48:10.280 align:middle line:84%
when the PK is going on
versus control or rest times.

00:48:10.280 --> 00:48:13.240 align:middle line:84%
Most of those things
are boring in a lab

00:48:13.240 --> 00:48:16.220 align:middle line:84%
and tough to do because
that one, for example,

00:48:16.220 --> 00:48:20.530 align:middle line:84%
is 48 seconds on, 48
seconds off, 48 seconds on

00:48:20.530 --> 00:48:24.220 align:middle line:84%
for hundreds trials in a row
after spending the half hour

00:48:24.220 --> 00:48:25.900 align:middle line:90%
getting that EEG on.

00:48:25.900 --> 00:48:29.500 align:middle line:84%
I'm a psychologist so I
looked at the motivation

00:48:29.500 --> 00:48:31.510 align:middle line:84%
to keep this really
juicy for people

00:48:31.510 --> 00:48:35.590 align:middle line:84%
so their performance would not
rise and then fall and become

00:48:35.590 --> 00:48:36.740 align:middle line:90%
boring to them.

00:48:36.740 --> 00:48:39.580 align:middle line:84%
And that's where the
Vegas stuff comes in.

00:48:39.580 --> 00:48:42.790 align:middle line:84%
Because it's definitely exciting
when you do it in Vegas and you

00:48:42.790 --> 00:48:45.580 align:middle line:84%
hit something at 200
million to 1 by chance.

00:48:45.580 --> 00:48:49.390 align:middle line:84%
You might also have some cash to
show as a prize for doing that.

00:48:49.390 --> 00:48:52.870 align:middle line:84%
In meditation, for example,
before I go to a slot machine,

00:48:52.870 --> 00:48:56.500 align:middle line:84%
I may visualize exactly what
I want, such as a royal flush

00:48:56.500 --> 00:48:57.430 align:middle line:90%
in hearts.

00:48:57.430 --> 00:49:01.930 align:middle line:84%
That's 160,000 to 1 by chance,
and I'll go down and hit it

00:49:01.930 --> 00:49:04.300 align:middle line:90%
in the first pull.

00:49:04.300 --> 00:49:07.450 align:middle line:84%
So that gives me proof
that this was real.

00:49:07.450 --> 00:49:08.530 align:middle line:90%
I've meditated.

00:49:08.530 --> 00:49:09.760 align:middle line:90%
I've raised my energy.

00:49:09.760 --> 00:49:13.870 align:middle line:84%
And when I go down, I'm also
checking intuition as the time

00:49:13.870 --> 00:49:17.290 align:middle line:84%
right now and is this
the machine to do it on.

00:49:17.290 --> 00:49:19.420 align:middle line:84%
>> If you wanted to
understand the data underlying

00:49:19.420 --> 00:49:21.760 align:middle line:84%
precognition, there's a bunch
of information out there.

00:49:21.760 --> 00:49:24.880 align:middle line:84%
Go to Google Scholar and just
look up precognitive abilities.

00:49:24.880 --> 00:49:26.980 align:middle line:84%
You could also look up
predictive anticipatory

00:49:26.980 --> 00:49:29.630 align:middle line:84%
activity to find any
of that information.

00:49:29.630 --> 00:49:31.240 align:middle line:90%
So go have at it.

00:49:31.240 --> 00:49:34.200 align:middle line:84%
If what that data
were about some kind

00:49:34.200 --> 00:49:36.330 align:middle line:84%
of new drug for some
kind of disease,

00:49:36.330 --> 00:49:38.970 align:middle line:84%
people would be taking
the drug for that disease.

00:49:38.970 --> 00:49:41.130 align:middle line:10%
My experience going
into the academic world

00:49:41.130 --> 00:49:42.720 align:middle line:10%
and giving talks
about this stuff

00:49:42.720 --> 00:49:45.150 align:middle line:10%
to, basically, people
who are largely

00:49:45.150 --> 00:49:48.898 align:middle line:10%
interested but skeptical, first
of all, they'll ask questions,

00:49:48.898 --> 00:49:50.190 align:middle line:10%
well, have you thought of this?

00:49:50.190 --> 00:49:51.270 align:middle line:10%
And often, they'll
have you thought

00:49:51.270 --> 00:49:53.070 align:middle line:10%
of this will be like the most
basic thing that, of course,

00:49:53.070 --> 00:49:53.730 align:middle line:10%
you thought of.

00:49:53.730 --> 00:49:55.440 align:middle line:84%
But they're just learning to
think about this so they're

00:49:55.440 --> 00:49:57.060 align:middle line:90%
going to-- they should ask.

00:49:57.060 --> 00:50:02.590 align:middle line:84%
But after the talk, they'll come
up to you and, one by one, say,

00:50:02.590 --> 00:50:04.320 align:middle line:90%
can I talk to you afterwards?

00:50:04.320 --> 00:50:05.880 align:middle line:90%
Can we just talk privately?

00:50:05.880 --> 00:50:07.560 align:middle line:84%
I just want to tell
you my experience

00:50:07.560 --> 00:50:09.933 align:middle line:84%
I had about this dream
that was so real,

00:50:09.933 --> 00:50:11.350 align:middle line:84%
and then it happened
the next day.

00:50:11.350 --> 00:50:13.350 align:middle line:84%
And then the next person,
can I just have your card?

00:50:13.350 --> 00:50:14.580 align:middle line:90%
And then you get an email--

00:50:14.580 --> 00:50:16.600 align:middle line:84%
I didn't want to say it
in front of anyone else,

00:50:16.600 --> 00:50:19.140 align:middle line:84%
but I had this experience
the night before my aunt died

00:50:19.140 --> 00:50:20.490 align:middle line:90%
and she wasn't sick and--

00:50:20.490 --> 00:50:22.470 align:middle line:84%
and then the next person,
and the next person.

00:50:22.470 --> 00:50:26.940 align:middle line:84%
And at some point, I started
saying, talk to each other.

00:50:26.940 --> 00:50:29.610 align:middle line:84%
You're all having
this experience.

00:50:29.610 --> 00:50:30.660 align:middle line:90%
Talk to each other.

00:50:30.660 --> 00:50:33.070 align:middle line:10%
>> The topic is
so controversial,

00:50:33.070 --> 00:50:35.080 align:middle line:10%
you cannot get it published.

00:50:35.080 --> 00:50:38.920 align:middle line:10%
We tried to send one paper
into a physics journal.

00:50:38.920 --> 00:50:43.390 align:middle line:84%
The editor thought it was fine,
but the publishers, the higher

00:50:43.390 --> 00:50:46.780 align:middle line:84%
ups, were very uncomfortable
with the topic.

00:50:46.780 --> 00:50:49.810 align:middle line:84%
Usually, when you send
a paper for publication,

00:50:49.810 --> 00:50:54.550 align:middle line:84%
they send it to two, maybe
three reviewers or referees.

00:50:54.550 --> 00:50:59.260 align:middle line:84%
Well, this paper went out to
something like 21 referees.

00:50:59.260 --> 00:51:01.660 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it was getting
really rather silly.

00:51:01.660 --> 00:51:04.360 align:middle line:84%
Until at one point, we
said, look, why don't we

00:51:04.360 --> 00:51:06.610 align:middle line:84%
just go with the majority
vote, at a point when

00:51:06.610 --> 00:51:08.830 align:middle line:90%
we knew we were one ahead.

00:51:08.830 --> 00:51:10.720 align:middle line:90%
And the paper got published.

00:51:10.720 --> 00:51:13.660 align:middle line:10%
>> I worked at the University
of Nevada in Las Vegas

00:51:13.660 --> 00:51:14.480 align:middle line:10%
for a while.

00:51:14.480 --> 00:51:16.570 align:middle line:10%
And so there, one of
the sociologists I knew

00:51:16.570 --> 00:51:19.990 align:middle line:10%
was studying prostitution
in Las Vegas.

00:51:19.990 --> 00:51:22.330 align:middle line:84%
Well, Las Vegas
businesspeople did not

00:51:22.330 --> 00:51:24.830 align:middle line:84%
like it to be known publicly
that this was going on,

00:51:24.830 --> 00:51:26.840 align:middle line:84%
even though everybody
knew that it was.

00:51:26.840 --> 00:51:29.680 align:middle line:84%
And so her ability to do
that research and publish it

00:51:29.680 --> 00:51:32.660 align:middle line:84%
was tamped down to the point
where she could not do it.

00:51:32.660 --> 00:51:34.720 align:middle line:84%
And that's just one
of many examples

00:51:34.720 --> 00:51:36.730 align:middle line:84%
where if there's some
community that says,

00:51:36.730 --> 00:51:40.540 align:middle line:84%
we don't want that to be out
there, they will stop it.

00:51:40.540 --> 00:51:43.090 align:middle line:84%
We can look back at tobacco
and all kinds of things

00:51:43.090 --> 00:51:46.240 align:middle line:84%
that were, at one
time, suppressed

00:51:46.240 --> 00:51:48.070 align:middle line:84%
for political or
business reasons.

00:51:48.070 --> 00:51:52.120 align:middle line:84%
And that's no different
in this domain.

00:51:52.120 --> 00:51:54.460 align:middle line:84%
>> There are some things that
are very hard to get with

00:51:54.460 --> 00:51:55.360 align:middle line:90%
remote viewing.

00:51:55.360 --> 00:51:59.770 align:middle line:10%
It's hard to get analytical
things like names or numbers

00:51:59.770 --> 00:52:00.970 align:middle line:10%
or dates.

00:52:00.970 --> 00:52:04.990 align:middle line:84%
But remote viewers are really
good at describing the sense

00:52:04.990 --> 00:52:06.940 align:middle line:90%
impressions about an object.

00:52:06.940 --> 00:52:11.110 align:middle line:84%
So, could you communicate
with a submarine

00:52:11.110 --> 00:52:14.680 align:middle line:90%
using associated imagery?

00:52:14.680 --> 00:52:16.450 align:middle line:90%
So I needed a submarine.

00:52:16.450 --> 00:52:18.760 align:middle line:84%
John Warner, who was the
Secretary of the Navy,

00:52:18.760 --> 00:52:21.610 align:middle line:84%
invited me to go up to
Groton, Connecticut with him.

00:52:21.610 --> 00:52:23.710 align:middle line:10%
And on the plane
was Hyman Rickover,

00:52:23.710 --> 00:52:26.290 align:middle line:10%
the father of the
American nuclear navy

00:52:26.290 --> 00:52:27.910 align:middle line:10%
and the nuclear submarines.

00:52:27.910 --> 00:52:31.240 align:middle line:84%
And I asked him if he would
let me do this experiment.

00:52:31.240 --> 00:52:33.113 align:middle line:84%
And he said, let
me get back to you.

00:52:33.113 --> 00:52:34.030 align:middle line:90%
Let me think about it.

00:52:34.030 --> 00:52:35.720 align:middle line:90%
He was quite interested in it.

00:52:35.720 --> 00:52:39.670 align:middle line:10%
And he called me, I don't
know, a week, 10 days later.

00:52:39.670 --> 00:52:43.400 align:middle line:10%
And he said, that's a really
interesting experiment

00:52:43.400 --> 00:52:44.590 align:middle line:10%
but I'm not going to do it.

00:52:44.590 --> 00:52:46.807 align:middle line:84%
It'll leak out, it'll
get a lot of attention,

00:52:46.807 --> 00:52:47.890 align:middle line:90%
and we just don't want it.

00:52:47.890 --> 00:52:49.700 align:middle line:84%
So I'm sorry, I'm
not going to do it.

00:52:49.700 --> 00:52:53.510 align:middle line:10%
>> I did a consulting job for
a big hotel chain that wanted

00:52:53.510 --> 00:52:57.770 align:middle line:10%
to integrate empathy
into their core values.

00:52:57.770 --> 00:52:58.820 align:middle line:90%
Real empathy.

