tuned in with another person.

00:53:09.080 --> 00:53:11.780 align:middle line:84%
And they were not
available to that message.

00:53:11.780 --> 00:53:15.530 align:middle line:84%
They wanted it in theory, but
in practice, it was a grind.

00:53:15.530 --> 00:53:18.530 align:middle line:10%
>> I know a lot of my colleagues
who have had their labs burned

00:53:18.530 --> 00:53:24.050 align:middle line:10%
down and their lives threatened
and things like that.

00:53:24.050 --> 00:53:27.570 align:middle line:84%
For some reason, I guess
my angels are working hard.

00:53:27.570 --> 00:53:31.540 align:middle line:10%
>> There's always a worldview
by which science is bounded more

00:53:31.540 --> 00:53:32.340 align:middle line:10%
or less.

00:53:32.340 --> 00:53:36.350 align:middle line:10%
But if you ask questions that
go beyond that conventional

00:53:36.350 --> 00:53:39.650 align:middle line:10%
worldview, you're out
there in frontier science.

00:53:39.650 --> 00:53:42.530 align:middle line:84%
>> I just have to be in the
lab and do the experiments

00:53:42.530 --> 00:53:44.990 align:middle line:84%
because most conventional
scientists won't.

00:53:44.990 --> 00:53:47.990 align:middle line:84%
>> It's different from what
some people might call fringe

00:53:47.990 --> 00:53:53.150 align:middle line:84%
science, which is really far
out topics that aren't necessary

00:53:53.150 --> 00:53:57.440 align:middle line:84%
